
What is NoSQL data base?

A NoSQL database provides a mechanism for storage and retrieval of data which is modeled in means other than the tabular relations used in relational databases. ... NoSQL databases are increasingly used in big data and real-time web applications.


How does data get stored in NoSQl database?
Key-value stores are the simplest NoSQL databases. Every single item in the database is stored as an attribute name (or 'key'), together with its value.


What is columm  family?

